description: oof +‎ -y. Oof is a clipping of ooftish, from Yiddish אויפֿן טיש‎ (oyfn tish, “on the table”) in the phrase געלט אויפֿן טיש‎ (gelt oyfn tish, “money on the table”).

adjectives.description: oofy (comparative more oofy, superlative most oofy)

entries.meaning: (Britain, slang, dated) Having lots of oof (money); rich, wealthy.
